55/* Bridge function to convert byte-oriented parser with line-oriented
56 * preprocessor.
57 */
58static size_t
59preproc_input(yasm_parser_gas *parser_gas, /*@out@*/ YYCTYPE *buf,
60 size_t max_size)
61{
62 size_t tot=0;
63 while (max_size > 0) {
64 size_t n;
65
66 if (!parser_gas->line) {
67 parser_gas->line = yasm_preproc_get_line(parser_gas->preproc);
68 if (!parser_gas->line)
69 return tot; /* EOF */
70 parser_gas->linepos = parser_gas->line;
71 parser_gas->lineleft = strlen(parser_gas->line) + 1;
72 parser_gas->line[parser_gas->lineleft-1] = '\n';
73 }
74
75 n = parser_gas->lineleft<max_size ? parser_gas->lineleft : max_size;
76 strncpy((char *)buf+tot, parser_gas->linepos, n);
77
78 if (n == parser_gas->lineleft) {
79 yasm_xfree(parser_gas->line);
80 parser_gas->line = NULL;
81 } else {
82 parser_gas->lineleft -= n;
83 parser_gas->linepos += n;
84 }
85
86 tot += n;
87 max_size -= n;
88 }
89 return tot;
90}

98static YYCTYPE *
99fill(yasm_parser_gas *parser_gas, YYCTYPE *cursor)
100{
101 yasm_scanner *s = &parser_gas->s;
102 int first = 0;
103 if(!s->eof){
104 size_t cnt = s->tok - s->bot;
105 if(cnt){
106 memmove(s->bot, s->tok, (size_t)(s->lim - s->tok));
107 s->tok = s->bot;
108 s->ptr -= cnt;
109 cursor -= cnt;
110 s->lim -= cnt;
111 }
112 if (!s->bot)
113 first = 1;
114 if((s->top - s->lim) < BSIZE){
115 YYCTYPE *buf = yasm_xmalloc((size_t)(s->lim - s->bot) + BSIZE);
116 memcpy(buf, s->tok, (size_t)(s->lim - s->tok));
117 s->tok = buf;
118 s->ptr = &buf[s->ptr - s->bot];
119 cursor = &buf[cursor - s->bot];
120 s->lim = &buf[s->lim - s->bot];
121 s->top = &s->lim[BSIZE];
122 if (s->bot)
123 yasm_xfree(s->bot);
124 s->bot = buf;
125 }
126 if((cnt = preproc_input(parser_gas, s->lim, BSIZE)) == 0) {
127 s->eof = &s->lim[cnt]; *s->eof++ = '\n';
128 }
129 s->lim += cnt;
130 if (first && parser_gas->save_input) {
131 int i;
132 YYCTYPE *saveline;
133 parser_gas->save_last ^= 1;
134 saveline = parser_gas->save_line[parser_gas->save_last];
135 /* save next line into cur_line */
136 for (i=0; i<79 && &s->tok[i] < s->lim && s->tok[i] != '\n'; i++)
137 saveline[i] = s->tok[i];
138 saveline[i] = '\0';
139 }
140 }
141 return cursor;
